correctness.rationale: Major schema and factual issues. (a) Numerous required numeric fields are null/None, violating the schema types and the “no nulls” rule: pressure.quantityValue.numericValue; thicknessControl.numberofCycles.quantityValue.numericValue; thicknessControl.filmThickness.quantityValue.numericValue; processParameters.filmThickness.quantityValue.numericValue; nucleationPeriod.quantityValue.numericValue; dosingTime/ purgeTime/ flowRates numericValues; multiple material/electrical property numericValues; deviceProperties.fieldEffectMobility.numericValue and onOffRatio.numericValue. (b) Unit violation: thicknessControl.growthPerCycle uses NanoM but schema requires ANGSTROM. (c) Unsubstantiated or placeholder values reduce traceability: reactantSelection.carrierGas and purgingGas = “Not Found” (article does not specify); processParameters.substrate = “Si wafer” is not stated in the article; saturation = false not supported; materialProperties.crystallinity.phase = “amorphous” not stated; otherAspects.filmStability = false and reproducibility = false not supported. (d) Misinterpretation: materialProperties.filmComposition.atomicRatio = “1:1:1” appears to copy the ALD cycle ratio rather than a measured atomic ratio (no composition data reported). (e) Duplicated/empty filmThickness fields (both under thicknessControl and processParameters) with null values violate schema. Correct entries include PEALD method for InOx/GaOx/ZnO, precursors (DADI/TMGa/DEZ), O2 plasma co-reactant, reactor name TFS200, temperature 250 °C, plasma power 38 W, and device Vth ≈ -3.5 V and SS ≈ 230 mV/dec. To correct: replace nulls with valid numbers or omit optional fields; fix GPC unit to Å (e.g., 2.1 Å/cycle); remove unsupported placeholders; do not report atomicRatio unless measured; only include substrate and other properties when explicitly stated.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is highly incomplete and contains multiple schema violations and untraceable values. Key issues: (1) Multiple processes described in the article are not represented: only IGZO PEALD is extracted, while the Al2O3 gate insulator (10 nm, PEALD at 250°C) and the IZO gate electrode (20 nm, PEALD/in-situ) ALD steps are missing; the study also explores different IGZO supercycle ratios and plasma powers that could be separate processes. (2) Numerous required numerical fields are populated with nulls (None), violating the schema: processParameters.pressure, thicknessControl.numberofCycles, thicknessControl.filmThickness, nucleationPeriod, dosingTime/purgeTime/flowRates (and only for InOx; GaOx and ZnO entries are missing), processParameters.filmThickness, and many material/device properties. (3) Unit non-compliance: thicknessControl.growthPerCycle is given as 0.21 nm, but the schema requires ANGSTROM; it should be ~2.1 Å. (4) Several values are ungrounded or factually incorrect: substrate set to “Si wafer” (not explicitly stated), saturation set to False without support, filmComposition.atomicRatio set to “1:1:1” though the article reports a cycle ratio, not a measured atomic ratio; crystallinity “amorphous” not reported; otherAspects (filmStability/reproducibility) set to False without evidence. (5) Material properties (uniformity variation %, conformality aspect ratio, roughness, density, optical/electrical film properties) are missing though some qualitative evidence exists; required fields are present but with nulls, violating the schema. (6) Device properties: Vth and SS are correctly extracted, but onOffRatio is left null despite Ion and Ioff being reported; field-effect mobility is missing. Overall, many required properties are missing or invalid, several entries are not traceable to the article, and multiple processes are omitted. Properties to add/review: add separate ALD processes for Al2O3 and IZO; provide valid numeric values and QUDT-compliant units (e.g., GPC in Å); remove/replace nulls; complete dosing/purge/flow for all sub-oxides or omit if the schema allows; correct atomicRatio to a measured composition (or omit if not reported); verify substrate; only include saturation/crystallinity/otherAspects if supported; extract film thickness/number of cycles from Fig. 5 if determinable; consider computing on/off ratio from reported Ion/Ioff.
